[~awithrow], 

In order to move to an HA CLC setup on a system that was upgraded before the second CLC is added there are some extra manual steps to be executed so database sync can be successful and the system is ready. We will need to drop a few legacy tables from the storage DB.

Follow existing instructions for adding the second CLC in a HA setup then perform the following on the second CLC:
# on the secondary CLC connect to the eucalyptus storage DB
{code}
psql -p 8777 -h ${EUCALYPTUS}/var/lib/eucalyptus/db/data eucalyptus_storage
{code}
# you will need to remove the following tables: aoemetainfo, aoevolumeinfo and storage_stats_info.
{code}
eucalyptus_storage=# DROP TABLE aoemetainfo;
DROP TABLE
eucalyptus_storage=# DROP TABLE aoevolumeinfo;
DROP TABLE
eucalyptus_storage=# DROP TABLE storage_stats_info;
DROP TABLE
{code}
# quit psql
{code}
eucalyptus_storage=# \q
{code}
# DB sync should now succeed. Note: it may take several minutes for the sync cycle to begin again and in the case of large amounts of data the initial sync may take a while.

An upgrade task for this is in a personal branch:

{code}
dev/sjones/EUCA-6462
{code}

This needs to be tested/merged once 3.4 is ready for upgrade testing.
